#: src-en/mod-appendix/metadata.xml:9
msgid "mod-appendix/metadata.xml$/dummyroot/metadata/title"
msgstr "RadiKal Sector"

#: src-en/mod-appendix/metadata.xml:19
msgid "mod-appendix/metadata.xml$/dummyroot/metadata/description"
msgstr ""
"A relatively small add-on for Multiverse 5.5.1, which adds a secret sector, many spicy augments (multi-ramming, fire-related, special hacking, repair, internal...), blue options, upgrades, sounds, visuals and combos!\n"
"Also features a few weapons and 4 ships (3 unlockable) with specific gimmicks.\n"
"The general theme is powerful but potentially dangerous (to you) experimental tech. More content coming soon!\n"
"\n"
"****** CONTENT ******\n"
"\t\n"
"\tRadiKal sector:\n"
"-Find the reroute coordinates during normal gameplay or buy a double agent from a shop to get those, then reroute as usual.\n"
"-It's full of danger, sacrifices and rare, powerful equipment! Will you dare enter?\n"
"\n"
"\tResource-hungry Combat Augments:\n"
"-Shipvore Ram: recklessly throw your ship at the enemy, disregarding your fuel reserves and the safety of your crew. \n"
"Combos with Fuel Conserver and Emergency Generator.\n"
"-Scorched Earth, for when you want to set your own ship on fire, and benefit from it.\n"
"Comes with upgrades, streamlining the experience and empowering your crew.\n"
"-Plasma Teleporter: immediately ignite the enemy ship!\n"
"Comes with a safe and a risky deployment method.\n"
"\n"
"\tOther Offensive Augments:\n"
"-Flammabilizer: deal with fireproof and resistant enemies!\n"
"-Charged Belts makes your crew damage the ship they're in on death.\n"
"-Vulnerabilizer: slowly remove the enemy's defenses, with some randomness.\n"
"\n"
"\tUtility augments:\n"
"-Enigmashin: gamble with fleet delays through briefly peaceful hacking.\n"
"-Oxygenizer: spawn an atmosphere at the start of fights.\n"
"\n"
"\tDefensive augments:\n"
"-Offense Disabler makes the enemy harmless for a few seconds, progressively restoring their power afterwards.\n"
"-Punk Harmony uses a bootleg Harmony to automate and empower your Engi, scaling with Mind Control and Hacking.\n"
"-Defense Kits make your crew much sturdier on your ship.\n"
"-A.E.R.A. Second Wind can automatically save your ship, once per purchase.\n"
"\n"
"\tInternal augments:\n"
"-Mind Heater: in fire, makes your crew resist Mind Control and stun, on both ships.\n"
"-Demicloners: provides a semblance of cloning when your crew dies without a Clonebay.\n"
"\n"
"\tCustom weapons:\n"
"-Bada fissure beam can deal massive damage to large systems, or blow up ships!\n"
"-Rain of Ions shoots all kinds of ions at once!\n"
"-Rain of Fire can eventually maintain multiple full strength fires against any ship!\n"
"-BPS Messenger heavy laser combines the strengths of all 3 RK subfactions.\n"
"\n"
"\tNew crew:\n"
"-Uptors are made out of Alpha Gouls to fit the needs of the RK Scorch.\n"
"\n"
"\t3 player ships with unique gimmicks!\n"
"-Embark on a wild ride with the Rammer, boasting a superior locked version of the Shipvore Ram.\n"
"-The Scorcher is outfitted with what you need to burn down any enemy.\n"
"-The Punker plays around its massive reactor, particle accelerator, and special hacking.\n"
"\n"
"****** Changelog ******\n"
"CHANGELOG RadiKal Sector v5.82g\n"
"-NOW REQUIRES FUSION LIBRARY.\n"
"-Improved some texts.\n"
"\n"
"* Augments\n"
"-Demicloner:\n"
"Is now Demicloners: new technology called backpacks allows it to work on both ships. (No I did not lose 3 trained Free Mantis and Ty'Erel while boarding Weapons in the giant auto boss of the ghost sector. Look, If I didn't do that it would have destroyed my ship, okay?)\n"
"Shell Radiants now demiclone into Shell Guardians instead of normal Shells.\n"
"\n"
"* Crew\n"
"- New (and first) RadiKal crew subtype, Uptor! Type: ghost. Good survivability, can set random rooms on fire remotely and affect system fire resistance. Demiclones into Phantom Goul Alpha but does not usually count as a Vagabond.\n"
"\n"
"* The RadiKal sector\n"
"-The event with Theocracy gear buyers and the equivalent Zoltan one are now unique (again).\n"
"-The RadiKal Deckhands section in stores was renamed RK Associates. The new RadiKals section is for crew exclusive to this add-on (with a discount).\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Special thanks to (in no particular order) Arc, Lizzard, codyfun, Qaser7, bamalf, Dr. Nauter, Witherbottom, Chooseche, Eschaton, Pepper, Untitled, Pupi, vertaalfout, Dalvest, Alder, Kix, [Enchanter], Pedrosian96, Royal Slime, [yenlo]R4V3-0N, robinthedragon2, Ehtya (Laythe), Blizz/mr_easy_money, Skye[NikoMaster], Julk, Felipe, marcrusian, Abstrusity and other people who helped on the FTL:MV Discord, for streaming the mod, and valuable information on balance, modding, coding and art.\n"
"\n"
"Feedback? Questions? @Dj0z in the Multiverse server on Discord\n"
"\n"
"Good luck and have fun!"
